You are working on TAW Theme — a classic WordPress theme with a custom block architecture.

Full architecture docs: see AGENTS.md in the repo root (start with its "Codex — Dense Reference" section).

# Core Concepts

| Fact | Detail |
|---|---|
| Blocks | `Blocks/{Name}/{Name}.php` — folder name MUST match class name |
| Two types | `MetaBlock` (owns metaboxes, fetches post_meta) / `Block` (presentational, receives props) |
| Discovery | `BlockLoader::loadAll()` auto-discovers — never manually register in `functions.php` |
| Rendering | `BlockRegistry::queue()` before `get_header()`, then `BlockRegistry::render()` in template body |
| PSR-4 (theme) | `TAW\Blocks\` → `Blocks/` only — that's the *only* mapping in this theme's `composer.json` |
| Everything else | `TAW\Core\*`, `TAW\Helpers\*`, `TAW\CLI\*` come from the `taw/core` composer package, PSR-4-mapped to `vendor/taw/core/src/` — never `inc/` |

`inc/` holds only theme-owned config (`options.php`, `performance.php`, `customizations.php`) and Metabox view templates — not framework classes.

# Stack

WordPress 6.0+, PHP 8.1+, Tailwind CSS v4 (`@tailwindcss/vite`, entry `resources/css/app.css`), Alpine.js v3, Vite v7 (dev server `localhost:5173`, builds to `public/build/`), SCSS via `sass` (`resources/scss/app.scss` global, `style.scss` per-block).

Bespoke metabox framework lives at `vendor/taw/core/src/Core/Metabox/Metabox.php` (not `inc/`).

# Creating a MetaBlock

1. `Blocks/{Name}/{Name}.php` extending `TAW\Blocks\MetaBlock`, `protected string $id = '{name}'`
2. Implement `registerMetaboxes()` — `new Metabox([...])`
3. Implement `getData(int|false $postId): array` — **exact signature required, missing `|false` is a whole-site fatal**
4. `Blocks/{Name}/index.php` — template receives extracted vars
5. Optional `style.css`/`style.scss` + `script.js` — auto-enqueued
6. **Required:** `tests/Unit/Blocks/{Name}Test.php` testing `getData()`'s hydration logic — AGENTS.md § "Testing Blocks"

# Creating a UI Block

1. `Blocks/{Name}/{Name}.php` extending `TAW\Blocks\Block`, `protected string $id = '{name}'`
2. Implement `defaults(): array`
3. `Blocks/{Name}/index.php` — receives merged props
4. Use directly: `(new Button())->render(['text' => 'Click'])`

# Metabox Framework

Field types: `text, textarea, wysiwyg, url, number, range, select, image, files, group, checkbox, color, repeater, post_select, datepicker`

Meta key pattern: `_taw_{field_id}`. Helpers: `Metabox::get($postId, $fieldId)`, `Metabox::get_image_url($postId, $fieldId)`. Features: tabs, `show_on` callbacks, `width` property, `sanitize => 'code'`.

Full field options / conditional logic / repeater nesting: AGENTS.md § "The Metabox Framework".

# Asset Pipeline

- Vite auto-discovers block assets in `vite.config.js` via `readdirSync`
- Dev: served from `localhost:5173`; prod: `manifest.json` → hashed files
- Block styles/scripts get `type="module"` via `script_loader_tag` filter
- Tailwind scans all PHP files via `@source` directive in `resources/css/app.css`

# Rules

- Never put block logic in `functions.php`
- Never call `wp_enqueue_style/script` directly for block assets
- Never mismatch folder name and class name
- Always `queue()` blocks before `get_header()` in templates
- Always escape output (`esc_html`, `esc_url`, `esc_attr`)
- After creating new PHP classes, run `composer dump-autoload`
- Never ship a new block without its unit test — run `composer run test` to confirm it actually passes

Full "Do NOT" list: AGENTS.md § "Do NOT".
